23/04/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- A mass grave containing 80 bodies has been unearthed in Ballsh, southwest Albania. The victims were allegedly killed by the communist regime between 1944 and 1991. The head of the Institute for Politically Persecuted, Simon Miraka, confirmed that the grave was found in February this year, media reported on Thursday (April 22nd). Reportedly, each set of remains had a bottle nearby containing the name of the victim. Another mass grave, this one located 5km outside Tirana, was also uncovered in February. (Lajmifundit, Ora News, News 24 - 22/04/10)
